modules.description: Transforms expressions using the |. or -> operator to pipe the left side as the first argument of the right side. Operates on OCaml and Reason syntax trees, modifying function application order. Enables concise function chaining in code written with pipeline syntax.

Provides a transformation function for parsing trees that enables inline data processing with a custom syntax. Operates on OCaml AST nodes, allowing for in-place modification during parsing. Used to inject pipeline-style operations directly into code during the compilation phase.
